abstract: SAN FRANCISCO, Sept. 2.--A special dispatch to the Chronicle from Tombstone, Arizona, says: "A rumor reached here to-day that the Mexican troops demanded of the American troops the release of Geronimo. abstract: BELFAST, Sept. 29.--There was desperate fighting to-day between Protestant and Catholic workmen at Barbour's foundry in this city. The police interfered, when the fighters joined forces and stoned and routed the police. Cavalry were then summoned, who charged upon and dispersed the mob. Scores of rioters and several policemen were injured.

abstract: WINNIPEG, Manitoba, Sept. 29.--The editor of the Fort MacLeod Gazette wires the Manitobian that no massacre by the Indians has occurred in the Northwest as reported in special dispatches from Ottawa, Ontario.
